    <title>RADService</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="namespaceRADService" kindref="compound">RADService</ref> contains deployment-oriented helpers:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>systemd unit generation and writing,</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>sd_notify-compatible ready/watchdog messages without libsystemd,</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>single-instance process locks via <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADLockFile" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADLockFile</ref></computeroutput>,</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>optional Unix daemonization for service-style programs.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>These helpers are useful for embedded appliances and desktop background tools that need reproducible service metadata. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
    <location file="docs/public/radservice.md"/>
  </compounddef>
</doxygen>
